Lack enough support: The claim lacks evidence or support to prove that either Trump or Biden actually said the quoted statement.
Contradict fact: The claim contradicts the fact that there is no evidence or record of either Trump or Biden saying the quoted statement.
Exaggerate: The claim exaggerates by attributing the statement to both Trump and Biden without any substantiated proof.
Problematic assumption: The claim assumes that the statement was made by either Trump or Biden, despite the lack of evidence.
Exist alternative explanation: There is an alternative explanation that the phrase "people are dying that have never died before" was already in use before being falsely attributed to Trump and Biden.
